text: The Interim National Assembly () was the legislative body of the Third Czechoslovak Republic from 28 October 1945 to June 1946. It had 300 members, all from the National Front. It was succeeded by the Constituent National Assembly, which sat for another two years before the democratic government was overthrown in the 1948 Czechoslovak coup d'état. ==References== Category:Defunct unicameral legislatures Category:Parliaments of Czechoslovakia Category:Provisional governments Category:1945 establishments in Czechoslovakia Category:1946 disestablishments in Czechoslovakia
